.TH "do_shash" 9 "do_shash" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
do_shash \- Do a synchronous hash operation in software
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" do_shash
.BI "(unsigned char *name "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *result "  ","
.BI "const u8 *data1 "  ","
.BI "unsigned int data1_len "  ","
.BI "const u8 *data2 "  ","
.BI "unsigned int data2_len "  ","
.BI "const u8 *key "  ","
.BI "unsigned int key_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
The name of the hash algorithm
.IP "result" 12
Buffer where digest is to be written
.IP "data1" 12
First part of data to hash. May be NULL.
.IP "data1_len" 12
Length of data1, in bytes
.IP "data2" 12
Second part of data to hash. May be NULL.
.IP "data2_len" 12
Length of data2, in bytes
.IP "key" 12
Key (if keyed hash)
.IP "key_len" 12
Length of key, in bytes (or 0 if non-keyed hash)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that the crypto API will not select this driver's own transform because
this driver only registers asynchronous algos.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if hash successfully stored in result
< 0 otherwise
